---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import StructuredData from '../../components/StructuredData.astro';

const comparisonData = {
  title: 'Mixo vs Webflow AI',
  description: 'Mixo vs Webflow: Which AI website builder is better? Compare budget-friendly simplicity vs powerful visual CMS with code export.',
  date: 'January 2025'
};

const tools = [
  {
    name: 'Mixo',
    score: 8.5,
    ease: 9.0,
    design: 8.0,
    speed: 9.0,
    flexibility: 8.0,
    value: 9.0,
    price: '$9-39/mo',
    features: ['Best value ($9/mo)', 'Fastest AI generation', 'Clean designs', 'All features included'],
    bestFor: 'Budget & ease',
    strengths: ['Unbeatable price', 'Very easy (9.0/10)', 'Fast setup', 'Great value'],
    weaknesses: ['Limited features', 'Basic CMS', 'No code export', 'Less powerful']
  },
  {
    name: 'Webflow',
    score: 8.5,
    ease: 7.0,
    design: 9.0,
    speed: 7.5,
    flexibility: 9.5,
    value: 7.5,
    price: '$15-59/mo',
    features: ['Powerful CMS (9.5/10)', 'Code export', 'Complete control', 'Professional hosting'],
    bestFor: 'Power users',
    strengths: ['Best flexibility (9.5/10)', 'Powerful CMS', 'Code export', 'Complete control'],
    weaknesses: ['Steep learning curve', 'Higher cost', 'Complex for beginners', 'Overkill for simple']
  }
];
---

<Layout title={`${comparisonData.title}: Which is Better?`} description={comparisonData.description}>
  <!-- FAQ Structured Data -->
  <StructuredData
    type="FAQPage"
    data={[
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is Mixo or Webflow better for website building?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Both Mixo and Webflow score 8.5/10 overall but serve completely different purposes. Mixo offers much better ease of use (9.0/10 vs 7.0/10), faster setup (9.0/10 vs 7.5/10), superior value for money (9.0/10 vs 7.5/10), and significantly more affordable pricing at $9/month vs $15/month. Webflow offers superior design quality (9.0/10 vs 8.0/10), much better flexibility (9.5/10 vs 8.0/10), powerful CMS capabilities (9.5/10), and code export capability that Mixo lacks. Mixo is better for: beginners, bloggers, portfolios, simple business sites, users wanting maximum value and ease. Webflow is better for: designers, agencies, complex content sites, power users wanting complete control. Choose Mixo for simplicity and value. Choose Webflow for power and flexibility if you're willing to learn it."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the price difference between Mixo and Webflow?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Mixo and Webflow have different pricing structures with Mixo being more affordable at entry levels. Mixo starts at $9/month for all features, $19/month for premium plans, up to $39/month for advanced features. Over 3 years, Mixo costs $324-1404 depending on plan level. Webflow starts at $15/month for basic sites, $29/month for CMS features, up to $59/month for advanced plans. Over 3 years, Webflow costs $540-2124 depending on plan level. For basic websites, Mixo is more affordable ($9 vs $15/month base pricing). For CMS features, the gap widens ($19 vs $29/month). Mixo's aggressive pricing makes it exceptional value for budget-conscious users who don't need Webflow's power. Webflow's higher pricing reflects its powerful CMS and flexibility - worth it for users who need those capabilities. For most users starting out, Mixo provides better value while Webflow justifies its premium with superior power and flexibility."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I export code from Mixo or Webflow?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Webflow offers code export on paid plans (CMS tiers and above), allowing you to export clean HTML, CSS, and JS to host elsewhere or continue development manually. Mixo does NOT offer code export - your website stays on Mixo's servers permanently and you're locked into their platform. This is a major difference if you care about owning your code or having flexibility to migrate platforms. With Webflow, you can export your code and move to custom development when ready. With Mixo, you're committed to their platform but get ease of use and affordability. If code export matters for your long-term strategy, Webflow is the clear winner. If you don't care about code export and want the easiest experience at the best price, Mixo is the better choice. Platform lock-in is the trade-off for Mixo's convenience and value pricing."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is Webflow too hard for beginners?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Webflow has a steep learning curve (7.0/10 ease) compared to Mixo (9.0/10 ease). The interface is complex with many panels, options, and concepts to learn. However, Webflow's power comes from this complexity - you get complete control over design, interactions, animations, and CMS. For complete beginners, Mixo is significantly easier. Generate your site, customize with simple options, publish. For those willing to invest time learning, Webflow's skills are highly valuable - Webflow developers earn $75-150/hour freelance. Consider: Mixo if you want results fast with minimal learning. Webflow if you want to develop a valuable skill and have time to invest in learning. Many designers spend 20-40 hours learning Webflow basics before feeling comfortable."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Does Webflow have better designs than Mixo?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Webflow has superior design quality (9.0/10 vs 8.0/10). Webflow's templates are crafted by professional designers with pixel-perfect attention to detail. The visual editor allows precise control over typography, spacing, colors, and responsive behavior. Mixo has clean, modern designs but less customization depth. Mixo's strength is speed - generate a professional site in minutes without design decisions. Webflow's strength is control - craft exactly the design you envision with pixel-perfect precision. For most users, Mixo's designs are perfectly adequate and much faster. For design professionals or those with specific design requirements, Webflow's superior design system and template quality justify the learning curve."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which has better CMS: Mixo or Webflow?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Webflow has a powerful CMS (9.5/10) while Mixo has basic CMS capabilities. Webflow CMS supports: complex content models with multiple fields, relational content between items, powerful filtering and sorting, dynamic content binding, collection pages with pagination, SEO-optimized URLs, and multi-language content structure. Mixo CMS supports: blog posts, basic content management, simple image handling, and basic categorization. If you're building content-heavy sites like blogs, news sites, documentation, or portfolios with complex filtering - Webflow CMS is essential. For simple blogs and basic content, Mixo's CMS is sufficient. Many businesses start on Mixo and migrate to Webflow when their content structure outgrows Mixo's basic capabilities."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I switch from Mixo to Webflow later?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Switching from Mixo to Webflow is difficult and requires rebuilding your site from scratch. Mixo doesn't export code - you can't download your HTML/CSS or migrate your design. You must: copy all content manually, recreate layouts in Webflow, re-upload all images, configure CMS structure, rebuild all interactions and animations. This migration typically takes 20-40 hours for a simple site, 60-100+ hours for complex sites. Real example: client spent 80 hours migrating a 25-page Mixo site to Webflow when they needed custom features Mixo couldn't provide. Total cost: $16,000 in development time. If there's ANY chance you'll need Webflow's power later, start with Webflow. The migration cost from Mixo to Webflow exceeds the price difference many times over. Mixo is perfect only if you're certain your needs won't change."
        }
      }
    ]}
  />

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO -->
